instruction: [INST] Analyze this file to learn MacBook motherboard repair. The 'definitions' section explains key technical terms. The 'threads' section contains real-world repair discussions. Use both sections to understand and learn how to troubleshoot MacBook issues. Posts from username 'larossmann' , 'dukefawks' , and '2informaticos' are posts from trusted experts.[/INST]

definitions.820-3302: What is 820-3302? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.
definitions.PP3V3_S5: What is PP3V3_S5? PP3V3_S5 is a 3.3v power rail when the system is in an S5 soft off power state.
definitions.PP3V42_G3H: What is PP3V42_G3H? PP3V42_G3H is a power rail present when the machine is in a G3H global system hardware off state and is the first rail that should be generated in Macbooks that use it. .
definitions.PP5V_S5: What is PP5V_S5? This is a 5v power rail that is present when the machine is in an S5 soft off state..

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3302</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> No light in first LED
threads.message:
Clean board sometimes first LED comes on and iMac powers on fine, but most times no first LED, when that is the case here are some voltages:

<SIGNAL>PP12V_G3H</SIGNAL>: 12V
<SIGNAL>PP3V42_G3H</SIGNAL>: 3.4V
<SIGNAL>PP12V_S5</SIGNAL>: 0V Diode mode 0.520
<SIGNAL>PP5V_S5</SIGNAL>: 0V Dione mode 0.375
<SIGNAL>PP3V3_S5</SIGNAL>: 0V Diode mode 0.135

Already replaced <CHIP>U7600</CHIP>, <TRANSISTOR>Q7880</TRANSISTOR>, <CHIP>U7880</CHIP>, <TRANSISTOR>Q7610</TRANSISTOR> and <TRANSISTOR>Q7650</TRANSISTOR> because I am tonto and was desperate, please help!

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3302</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> No light in first LED
<LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3302</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> No light in first LED
threads.message: Replaced <TRANSISTOR>Q7950</TRANSISTOR> but same thing, but that lead me to study that circuit and realized <CHIP>U7950</CHIP> was the problem, board is happy and running again, thanks!
